-- SSP Energy to sell up to $75.2 mln of shares in APR Energy - source
-- By Freya Berry
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 12:20PM EDT
-- None



LONDON, April 10 (Reuters) - British electricity provider APR Energy <APREN.L> is aiming to sell up to 44.8 million pounds ($75.2 million) of shares, after a source familiar with the deal said on Thursday that the company had priced the placement at 790-800 pence per share.

Goldman Sachs <GS.N>, which is running the accelerated bookbuilding process, said earlier that shareholder SSP Energy was selling down up to 5.6 mln ordinary shares in the company.